# Preserve skill runbook structure

When editing a skill `SKILL.md`, **respect the existing structure**. Do not renumber,
reorder, insert, merge, or split phases just to emphasize a single point.

## Do

- Strengthen clarity **inside** the existing step, checklist item, or section
- Add a short callout or hard-rule blurb that **references** current step numbers
- Update linked references to match wording — not a new step order

## Do not

- Renumber the phase checklist or `## N.` sections for one concern (e.g. cleanup)
- Move a step earlier/later in the runbook unless the user explicitly asks to restructure
- Invent parallel step schemes (e.g. “start of run” as a new numbered phase) when an
  existing step already covers that work

If a structural change is truly required, ask the user first and keep the rest of the
runbook’s shape intact.
